<section>
<section id="slide-orgb7effff">
<h2 id="orgb7effff">Mobility and labor shocks</h2>
<ul>
<li>We saw that moving can have large benefits for workers, but mostly for younger people and their children</li>
<li>But even when jobs disappear, people don't move very frequently</li>
<li>Negative shocks can be long-lasting</li>
<li>Low intergenerational mobility means these shocks can persist for decades</li>
<li>Policy?</li>

</ul>
</section>
